Ten days were employed in &s;upplying the $leet with wood
and water, in waiting for the ho&s;pital &s;hip in reviews, re|embarkations,
councils of war, a&s;&s;emblies of the council
belonging to the i&s;land, in i&s;&s;uing proclamations, and
beating up for volunteers. At length, every great &s;hip
