adily u&s;e their utmo&s;t endeavours to &s;upport tho&s;e his wi&s;e and &s;alutary purpo&s;es, that the throne may be &s;treng$$$$ religion and morality encouraged, faction and corruption de&s;troyed, the pruity and e&s;&s;ence of parliament re&s;tored, and the happine&s;s and welfare of our con&s;titution pre&s;erved. When the above an&s;wer was returned to the Prince, there were pre&s;ent. <HI>The Duke of B.&mdash;The Earl of L.&mdash;The Earl of S.&mdash;The Earl of T.&mdash;The Earl of W.&mdash;The Earl of S.&mdash;Lord F.&mdash;Lord W.&mdash;Sir Wat. Wi$ Wynne.&mdash;Sir $ohn $. C.&mdash;Sir Walter B.&mdash;Sir Robert G.&mdash;Mr. F.&mdash;Mr. P.&mdash;Mr. $.</HI></NOTE>.</P>
